**Reject whitespace-only `--review-subagent` values.**

Line 206 currently allows values like `"   "`, which contradicts the “non-blank agent identifier” contract and can pass invalid config downstream.  


<details>
<summary>Suggested fix</summary>

```diff
     if (value === '--review-subagent') {
       const raw = argv[index + 1];

       if (!raw || raw.startsWith('--')) {
         throw new Error(
           'Pass --review-subagent <agent> with a non-blank agent identifier.',
         );
       }

-      reviewSubagent = raw;
+      const trimmed = raw.trim();
+      if (trimmed.length === 0) {
+        throw new Error(
+          'Pass --review-subagent <agent> with a non-blank agent identifier.',
+        );
+      }
+      reviewSubagent = trimmed;
       index += 1;
       continue;
     }
```
</details>

